def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    level_numbers = []
    for level in clocs:
        try:
            number = index._get_level_number(level)
            level_numbers.append(number)
        except KeyError:
            raise KeyError(f'Level {level} not found')

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in level_numbers]

    cnames = [index.names[i] for i in level_numbers]
    rnames = [index.names[i] for i in rlocs]

    if rlocs == []:
        # Everything is in clocs, so the dummy df has a regular index
        dummy_index = Index(obs_ids, name="__placeholder__")
    else:
        dummy_index = MultiIndex(
            levels=index.levels + [obs_ids],
            codes=index.codes + [comp_ids],
            names=index.names + ["__placeholder__"],
            verify_integrity=False,
        )

    if isinstance(data, Series):
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index

        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)

        columns = unstacked.index.set_names(cnames)
        unstacked.index = columns

    else:
        dummy = data.copy()
        dummy.index = dummy_index

        unstacked = dummy.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)

        columns = unstacked.columns.set_names(cnames)
        unstacked.columns = columns

    return unstacked
